article.headline: Southern Methodist 76, Paul Quinn 54
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Ike Ofoegbu scored 18 points and Bamba Fall had a career-high 12 rebounds to help lead Southern Methodist to a 76-54 win over Paul Quinn on Monday night. Devon Pearson and Donatas Rackauskas each added 11 points for the Mustangs (5-1). Fall came off the bench to add nine points. Tyrone Edwards came off the bench to lead Paul Quinn with 12 points. He was the team's only player to score in double figures. The Mustangs dominated the first half, leading 38-17 at the break. The Mustangs shot 43 percent for the game. Paul Quinn shot 35 percent for the game, improving from 23 percent in the first half to 45 percent in the second half.
